thread.title: Police seek help in Lawrenceville shooting deaths
thread.title_full: Police seek help in Lawrenceville shooting deaths

author: Steve Burns
title: Police seek help in Lawrenceville shooting deaths
text:
Lawrenceville police and Crime Stoppers are asking for the publicâ€™s help in finding information about the shooting deaths of two men.
About 2 a.m. Saturday, officers responding to a shooting found the bodies of Timothy Rogers and Ricky Johnson at the Crossland Economy Suites on West Pike Street, police said Tuesday.
More information about the victims or the incident was not released.
Anyone with information about the case is asked to contact Lawrenceville police at 770-670-5120. Tipsters can remain anonymous, and be eligible for rewards of up to $2,000, by contacting Crime Stoppers at 404-577-8477, texting information to 274637 or visiting crimestoppersatlanta.org .
